title.narrative: 2.4 MULTI-SECTOR NUTRITION PLAN MINISTRIES AND PARTNERS HAVE INCREASED CAPACITY T

description.narrative: 2.4 Multi-Sector Nutrition Plan sector Ministries and partners have increased capacity to legislate, plan and budget to improve nutrition interventions, including mainstreaming DRR to plan for, respond to and mitigate the effects of disasters, which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition In Early Childhood (Covid), Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 2. Nutrition: By 2022, children including adolescent girls and women of reproductive age have improved and equitable access to and use of adequate nutritious diet and improved nutritional care behaviour and care practices.
